Example Registration ID: USE-12345678-001

Note: If your Registration ID starts with SLS you may need to to select the Sales and Use Tax Form ST-9.","Destination":"RegistrationId","Required":true,"SkyscraperValidationRequired":false,"HideForFilingMethodId":null,"HideForFilingMethod":null,"DataType":"STRING","MaxLength":16,"Regex":"^[U][S][E][-]\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d[-]\d\d\d$","FilingQuestionCode":"MassachusettsUTStateRegId","JsonPath":"TaxpayerProfile.StateRegistrationId","InternalOnly":false,"SkyscraperFieldName":null,"DefaultAnswer":"","InlineHelpText":null,"PlaceholderText":null}

{"FilingQuestionId":21001434,"SortOrder":4,"Question":"Ohio UUT 1 Vendor's License Number","HelpText":"Find your vendor's license number by checking the documentation you received when you registered your business for a vendor’s license in Ohio.  A taxpayer cannot file a sales or use tax return using their Social Security number or FEIN.      Vendor’s license numbers that have a prefix of 95 or 96 are not sales or use tax accounts.   <br><br>
If your vendor’s license number has a prefix of 97 or 98, you should file the UUT 1 return for consumer use tax. <br><br>

Example vendor's license number: 97-123456","Destination":"RegistrationId","Required":true,"SkyscraperValidationRequired":false,"HideForFilingMethodId":null,"HideForFilingMethod":null,"DataType":"STRING","MaxLength":9,"Regex":"^((97|98)-\d{6})$","FilingQuestionCode":"OhioUUT1Vendor'sLicenseNumber","JsonPath":"TaxpayerProfile.StateRegistrationId","InternalOnly":false,"SkyscraperFieldName":null,"DefaultAnswer":"","InlineHelpText":null,"PlaceholderText":null}

{"FilingQuestionId":250,"SortOrder":3,"Question":"Pennsylvania CSP Id","HelpText":"The Pennsylvania CSP registration ID is 9 characters. It should start with either an S or a SC

Example: S00123456
or SC0012345 (specific to PA CSP only customers who aren't given a registration Id or SSTID)","Destination":"RegistrationId","Required":true,"SkyscraperValidationRequired":false,"HideForFilingMethodId":null,"HideForFilingMethod":null,"DataType":"STRING","MaxLength":9,"Regex":"","FilingQuestionCode":"PACSPID","JsonPath":"TaxpayerProfile.StateRegistrationId","InternalOnly":false,"SkyscraperFieldName":null,"DefaultAnswer":"","InlineHelpText":null,"PlaceholderText":null}

{"FilingQuestionId":89,"SortOrder":1,"Question":"Tennessee Account Number","HelpText":"Find your account number by checking the documents you received when you registered your business to collect and remit sales and use tax in Tennessee. <br> <br>

Example account numbers: 0123456789-SLC, 0123456789-STV, 0123456789-LBD or 0123456789-BUS <br> <br>
If you have a sales tax account, your account number should end with the letters SLC.  If you have a TV & Telecom account, your account number should end with the letters STV.  If you have a Liquor By The Drink Tax account, your account number should end with the letters LBD. If you have a Business Tax account, your account number should end with the letters BUS.","Destination":"RegistrationId","Required":true,"SkyscraperValidationRequired":false,"HideForFilingMethodId":null,"HideForFilingMethod":null,"DataType":"STRING","MaxLength":14,"Regex":"^\d{9,10}-(SLC|STV|LBD|BUS)$","FilingQuestionCode":"TennesseeAccountNo.","JsonPath":"TaxpayerProfile.StateRegistrationId","InternalOnly":false,"SkyscraperFieldName":null,"DefaultAnswer":null,"InlineHelpText":null,"PlaceholderText":null}

